  "abstract": "Corrects the wrong defaults a capable model has when writing tRPC v11, pinned to 11.18.0. Covers the v10-to-v11 drift that leaves stale code compiling but wrong — the React client flipping to @trpc/tanstack-react-query, transformers moving into links, renamed type exports, observable subscriptions replaced by async generators over SSE — alongside the defaults that are unsafe rather than merely stale, such as uncapped batching, CDN cache headers that cross users, and middleware ordered ahead of input validation.",
